Waterstone, Mamut Working on Offer for Book Chain, Observer Says

-- B y   J o h n   G l o v e r
-- 
2011-03-27T11:30:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-27/waterstone-mamut-working-on-offer-for-book-chain-observer-says.html
Tim Waterstone, founder of the U.K.
book chain that bears his name, is working with Russian
billionaire Alexander Mamut on an offer for the company, which
is owned by  HMV Group Plc (HMV) , the Observer said, without saying
where it got the information.  The business is expected to sell for about 75 million
pounds ($120 million), the newspaper said.  Click here for web link.   To contact the reporter on this story:
